## Existing Tool Restriction Section in Boss Agent

The Boss agent has an explicit section called **"Why Your Tools Are Scoped"** (lines 16-23 of the committed file) that documents the restrictions in plain language:

- Cannot read source files (routing work to specialists)
- Cannot use send-keys except to 1.0 (messaging system, not terminal control)
- Cannot spawn Agent instances (team infrastructure handles coordination)
- CAN access: `.doey/tasks/*`, `/tmp/doey/*`, `$RUNTIME_DIR/*`, `$DOEY_SCRATCHPAD`, `AskUserQuestion`

---

## Communication Patterns in Boss Agent

1. **User -> Boss**: User talks directly to Boss at pane 0.1
2. **Boss -> Taskmaster**: Via `doey msg send --to 1.0 --from 0.1` with structured subjects (`dispatch_task`, etc.)
3. **Boss -> User**: Plain text for status/reports, `AskUserQuestion` for questions
4. **Taskmaster -> Boss**: Via messages (subjects: `task_complete`, `question`, `status_report`, `error`)
5. **Boss checks messages**: `doey msg read --pane 0.1` on every turn, with trigger file fast path
6. **Boss observes panes**: `tmux capture-pane` for status checks (read-only)
7. **Boss health-checks Taskmaster**: Status check + nudge before every message send

